-- Taiwan Stock Movers: TPK Holding, United Microelectronics
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-07-10T05:54:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-10/taiwan-stock-movers-compal-electronics-united-microelectronics.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The  Taiex Index (TWSE)  fell 0.8 percent to 7,251.35, its fourth
day of losses and the biggest drop since June 8.  TPK Holding Co. (3673)  (3673 TT) slumped 6.9 percent to NT$330,
the most since June 1. The touch panel company’s revenue dropped
3.9 percent to NT$11.08 billion ($369.86 million) in June from a
year earlier, according to a statement on the company website.  United Microelectronics Corp. (2303)  (2303 TT), the world’s
second-largest custom maker of chips, climbed 0.8 percent to
NT$12.40. June sales rose 1.1 percent from a year earlier to
NT$9.29 billion, the first increase in more than a year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
